"{\"title\": \"STORYTELLING IN INTERACTIVE MEDIA AND GAMES\", \"level\": \"1002\", \"abbreviation\": \"IMGD\", \"description\": \"Cat. I \\n\\nThis course explores different types of story within gaming and other interactive\\nmedia. It delineates between linear, branching, and emergent storytelling, \\nidentifies hybrids, and finds new modes of making compelling narrative. A \\nvariety of games are discussed, including early text-based adventures, role-playing \\ngames, shooters, and strategy games. Students will construct characters situations, and narratives through game play and scripted cut scenes. Students \\nwill explore and use visual storytelling techniques.\", \"req\": [], \"cat1Status\": true, \"startYear\": -1}"